observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
instruct the Municipal Assessor and Municipal Accountant to submit the aforementioned lacking documents in compliance with Item 13.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001;
secure an Appraisal Report from an independent Appraisal Committee in provincial level;
prioritize the registration and transfer of title of the parcels of land to the municipal government to ensure ownership and to fully protect the interest of the government; and
henceforth, all claims against government funds shall be supported with complete documentation as required under Section 4(6) of PD No. 1445.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
instruct the BAC to adhere strictly to the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 in all stages of procurement process and ensure that all bid documents are complete and evaluated;
require the BAC to submit all lacking bid documents to the Audit Team;
instruct the Municipal Accountant to scrutinize every voucher for the completeness and veracity of supporting documents prior to processing of claims for payment of the above infrastructure projects in compliance with Section 4(6) of P.D. No. 1445.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
instruct the BAC to adhere strictly to the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of  R.A. No. 9184 in all stages of procurement process and ensure that all bid documents are complete and evaluated;
require the BAC to submit all lacking bid documents to the Audit Team;
require the Municipal Engineer to justify the ABC and submit the lacking Plans and Drawings for the above project; and
instruct the Municipal Accountant to submit the CAF and to scrutinize every voucher for the completeness and veracity of supporting documents prior to processing of claims for payment of the above infrastructure projects in compliance with Section 4.6 of P.D. No. 1445.
